29/11/2006
TIRANA, Albania -- The suspicious deaths of three chickens in the northern city of Kukes may mark the return of bird flu, according to press reports Wednesday (November 29th) in Tirana. The Directorate of Agriculture and Food is looking into the issue after being approached by local residents. According to Veterinary Research Institute experts, now that the migratory season has begun, bird flu is a possibility. Earlier this year, the deadly H5N1 virus strain was detected in poultry raised near the border with Greece. (Albanian News - 29/11/06)
